        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1050397214" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13042373311403803493"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1451286024i/17524875._SX540_.jpg' width='400' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6539257.The_Heart_of_a_Woman' title='The Heart of a Woman by Maya Angelou' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Heart of a Woman</a> is <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3503.Maya_Angelou' title='Maya Angelou' rel='nofollow noopener'>Maya Angelou</a>&apos;s forth autobiography. This book reveals more of <i>Maya</i>&apos;s hectic adventures, political opinions, struggle with racism, and misfortune in the romance department. You will be introduced to <i>Maya</i>, the activist, who works for <i>Martin Luther King Jr.</i> and gets to meet <i>Malcolm X</i>. I like that each chapter is exciting enough to keep me interested.<br/><br/>I&apos;m not surprised that she was able to keep her writing fresh and crispy with just the right amount of tasteful humor. Her son,</span>
  <span id="freeText13042373311403803493" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1451286024i/17524875._SX540_.jpg" width="400" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6539257.The_Heart_of_a_Woman" title="The Heart of a Woman by Maya Angelou" rel="nofollow noopener">The Heart of a Woman</a> is <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3503.Maya_Angelou" title="Maya Angelou" rel="nofollow noopener">Maya Angelou</a>'s forth autobiography. This book reveals more of <i>Maya</i>'s hectic adventures, political opinions, struggle with racism, and misfortune in the romance department. You will be introduced to <i>Maya</i>, the activist, who works for <i>Martin Luther King Jr.</i> and gets to meet <i>Malcolm X</i>. I like that each chapter is exciting enough to keep me interested.<br><br>I'm not surprised that she was able to keep her writing fresh and crispy with just the right amount of tasteful humor. Her son, <i>Guy</i>, is all grownup now and their mother/son relationship is heartwarming. She generously shares intimate details, so openly and honestly as per usual, which could be valuable life lessons on autonomy, relationships, and decision making for all women out there.<br><br>__________<br> <br><b>
  <u> Maya Angelou's Autobiographies:</u>
