        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2543792112" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15402519523309457729">I have to say, of all of Maya Angelou&apos;s biographies I&apos;ve read so far, this is my least favorite. The pacing felt a bit off and themes changed too abruptly. Still, it&apos;s a good book. I loved some parts of it, like the Billie Holiday story, or the time she confronted a white woman who came to watch her play but couldn&apos;t bear to think about her actions in the real world. I also loved how she depicted her mysoginistic lovers, and the way she reacts to them. And of course, I&apos;m still shocked by her ama</span>
  <span id="freeText15402519523309457729" style="display:none">I have to say, of all of Maya Angelou's biographies I've read so far, this is my least favorite. The pacing felt a bit off and themes changed too abruptly. Still, it's a good book. I loved some parts of it, like the Billie Holiday story, or the time she confronted a white woman who came to watch her play but couldn't bear to think about her actions in the real world. I also loved how she depicted her mysoginistic lovers, and the way she reacts to them. And of course, I'm still shocked by her amazing, extraordinarily adventurous life. I just felt that the sum of the parts wasn't as satisfactory as the parts on their own.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15402519523309457729" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
